1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:46,040
He's wounded, but he won't give up...

3
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,670
That bastard...

4
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,540
Anyway, I just need to follow
this trail of blood...

5
00:02:02,180 --> 00:02:05,140
Give me back my sword, damn it!

6
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:11,560
What the hell is this place?

7
00:02:11,610 --> 00:02:15,910
Once a Fox

8
00:02:12,230 --> 00:02:15,900
The samurai followed that
huge warrior monk...?

9
00:02:15,910 --> 00:02:19,830
Bandit's

Bridge

10
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:19,820
Who was that monk anyway?

11
00:02:20,570 --> 00:02:24,540
In spite of everything,
I'm so glad you're safe, Kawamatsu.

12
00:02:24,540 --> 00:02:28,920
I couldn't be more grateful for your concern–

13
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:33,880
Stand back, Your Majesty!

14
00:02:35,210 --> 00:02:39,340
That bastard Kaido... He's relentless
in his hunt for remnants like us!

15
00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:42,220
Hey, look over there!

16
00:02:42,220 --> 00:02:43,850
They've been annihilated!

17
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:46,180
Fill him full of lead!

18
00:02:50,140 --> 00:02:51,270
Kappa Style:

19
00:02:51,810 --> 00:02:53,860
Yorikiri!

20
00:03:00,910 --> 00:03:02,410
Kawamatsu!

21
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:06,370
Kawamatsu! Kawamatsu!

22
00:03:06,370 --> 00:03:07,370
Your Highness!

23
00:03:07,370 --> 00:03:09,750
Kawamatsu, are you hurt?

24
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,330
You need not fret over me.

25
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:16,920
More pursuers may be on their way.

26
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:19,220
We should depart from this place.

27
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:24,640
Hop on! The path ahead is treacherous.

28
00:03:26,140 --> 00:03:30,060
Wait just a minute! I am not
a child anymore, Kawamatsu!

29
00:03:31,730 --> 00:03:33,100
Is that so?

30
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:36,770
Well, adults do not get all pouty like blowfish.

31
00:03:36,770 --> 00:03:38,610
Stop, you are teasing me.

32
00:03:41,070 --> 00:03:43,570
I truly missed this.

33
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:47,910
I cannot believe that I am once again
walking alongside Her Highness.

34
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:52,540
There is so much I want to talk
to you about, but first, why are you here?

35
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:58,000
After you disappeared, I made
my way here on mundane business...

36
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:03,380
This northern land of Ringo,
just like its neighbor Hakumai,

37
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:09,100
was governed by the Shimotsuki Clan
who were well known for their hardiness.

38
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:12,480
The daimyo's name was
Lord Shimotsuki Ushimaru.

39
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:17,190
He was a master swordsman
with a fox companion ever by his side.

40
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:18,570
A fox?

41
00:04:18,570 --> 00:04:25,950
However, Ringo was another region
that fell victim to Kaido's destruction.

42
00:04:26,490 --> 00:04:31,950
Your Highness, are you familiar with Ringo's
tradition of creating the Eternal Graves?

43
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:34,340
Yes, the bodies within the caskets here

44
00:04:34,340 --> 00:04:37,540
keep from decaying for centuries due to the cold.

45
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:42,760
Correct. Moreover, the graves
are always marked by swords.

46
00:04:43,340 --> 00:04:47,600
At birth, the people of Ringo
are bestowed swords.

47
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:51,020
These blades are by their sides
from youth into old age.

48
00:04:51,020 --> 00:04:55,650
In death, the swords they
once carried mark their graves.

49
00:04:55,650 --> 00:04:58,860
They are with their blades for eternity.

50
00:04:58,860 --> 00:05:02,490
That is why their resting place
is called the Eternal Graves.

51
00:05:03,820 --> 00:05:09,780
However, some of the blades here are named,
so grave robbery is a constant issue.

52
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:13,680
It is part and parcel of
the region known as Ringo...

53
00:05:15,210 --> 00:05:20,130
Allow this one to tell you what happened
when I came here thirteen years ago...

54
00:05:29,740 --> 00:05:33,480
If I were to undergo harakiri,
I had decided it would be in this region...

55
00:05:42,530 --> 00:05:46,240
Damn! What is it, a monster?! How creepy!

56
00:05:47,820 --> 00:05:50,240
We'll get the weapons next time! Run!

57
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,700
Is this the curse of the Ringo samurai?!

58
00:05:58,670 --> 00:06:03,750
What a bother. Can they
at least let me die in peace?

59
00:06:10,340 --> 00:06:11,680
It is you!

60
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:15,520
Yes. I have met you once before!

61
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:20,480
You must be Onimaru!

62
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:24,570
That lion fox's name was Onimaru.

63
00:06:24,570 --> 00:06:29,780
He was the companion of Lord Shimotsuki
Ushimaru, the late daimyo of Ringo.

64
00:06:39,460 --> 00:06:45,710
This... Have you been
protecting this all by yourself?

65
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:49,100
In the more than five years since Ringo's fall,

66
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:56,180
Onimaru stood alone in the fight against those
who would rob the weapons of the Eternal Graves.

67
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:59,570
Now then, you have nothing to fear.

68
00:06:59,570 --> 00:07:01,600
I am an ally.

69
00:07:05,780 --> 00:07:07,900
You are injured...!

70
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:17,790
Onimaru! Stay with me!

71
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,090
You are awake!

72
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:34,470
Here, I have brought you food!

73
00:07:34,470 --> 00:07:37,500
I heard foxes love fried tofu.

74
00:07:41,350 --> 00:07:45,560
What is the matter? If you
do not eat, that wound will not heal.

75
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,940
You need to live to protect
your master's grave.

76
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:52,610
Just take a bite. Come on, try it.

77
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:05,000
My, I have a stomachache.
I must have overeaten!

78
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:11,340
It matters not, though!

79
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:13,510
Come, now! Do not hold back.

80
00:08:28,570 --> 00:08:30,690
Oh! Do you like it?!

81
00:09:08,310 --> 00:09:10,940
Onimaru, settle down.

82
00:09:13,690 --> 00:09:15,780
Forgive me! I know what it looks like!

83
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,620
Let go!

84
00:09:28,290 --> 00:09:31,130
How can I explain this to you?

85
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:35,170
I do not wish to disturb the dead as they rest!

86
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:40,060
But I have to act now!

87
00:09:42,770 --> 00:09:45,850
You must escape... to the future.

88
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:03,950
Thirteen years from now,
a great battle will begin anew!

89
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:12,920
Listen to me!

90
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:18,300
The day will come when samurai across
the nation will rally and stand proud!

91
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:23,350
At that time, we will have need
for an abundance of swords!

92
00:10:23,350 --> 00:10:30,440
On the battlefield, warriors advance
using the weapons of their fallen comrades!

93
00:10:30,980 --> 00:10:37,360
The souls residing within these blades will
empower samurai to better slay their foe!

94
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:41,910
This is still a battlefield!

95
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,910
Listen to me, Onimaru!

96
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:49,870
The battle between the Beast Pirates
and Wano is not yet over!

97
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:53,590
It is still too early to lay these swords to rest!

98
00:10:53,590 --> 00:11:01,390
Until that day comes, we cannot permit any
robbers to lay their hands on these weapons!

99
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:05,560
Instead, I will collect all of them...

100
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:07,980
and hide them away!

101
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:13,020
I... realize...

102
00:11:13,020 --> 00:11:18,610
that is the undertaking I now must complete!

103
00:11:24,030 --> 00:11:29,410
Your Highness... Princess Hiyori!

104
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:41,550
I could not protect Princess Hiyori...

105
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:44,510
but at least...

106
00:11:45,220 --> 00:11:50,430
I should be able to do this!

107
00:11:52,060 --> 00:11:56,690
I must occupy myself with a task
lest I am tormented to death by remorse...

108
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:58,860
If you are hungry,

109
00:11:58,860 --> 00:12:02,990
then just bite off my arm and let me be!

110
00:12:02,990 --> 00:12:07,120
I will not stop robbing these graves!

111
00:12:36,230 --> 00:12:36,270
Shimotsuki

